151 enum KindTy { ----
152 k_Token, ----
153 k_Register, ----
154 k_Immediate, ----
155 // SX-Aurora ASX form is disp(index, base). ----
156 k_MemoryRegRegImm, // base=reg, index=reg, disp=imm ----
157 k_MemoryRegImmImm, // base=reg, index=imm, disp=imm ----
158 k_MemoryZeroRegImm, // base=0, index=reg, disp=imm ----
159 k_MemoryZeroImmImm, // base=0, index=imm, disp=imm ----
160 // SX-Aurora AS form is disp(base). ----
161 k_MemoryRegImm, // base=reg, disp=imm ----
162 k_MemoryZeroImm, // base=0, disp=imm ----
163 // Other special cases for Aurora VE ----
164 k_CCOp, // condition code ----
165 k_RDOp, // rounding mode ----
166 k_MImmOp, // Special immediate value of sequential bit stream of 0 or 1. ----
167 } Kind; ----

417 void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override { 0
418 switch (Kind) { 0
419 case k_Token: 0
420 OS << "Token: " << getToken() << "\n"; 0
421 break; 0
422 case k_Register: 0
423 OS << "Reg: #" << getReg() << "\n"; 0
424 break; 0
425 case k_Immediate: 0
426 OS << "Imm: " << getImm() << "\n"; 0
427 break; 0
428 case k_MemoryRegRegImm: 0
429 assert(getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
430 OS << "Mem: #" << getMemBase() << "+#" << getMemIndexReg() << "+" 0
431 << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
432 break; 0
433 case k_MemoryRegImmImm: 0
434 assert(getMemIndex() != nullptr && getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
435 OS << "Mem: #" << getMemBase() << "+" << *getMemIndex() << "+" 0
436 << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
437 break; 0
438 case k_MemoryZeroRegImm: 0
439 assert(getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
440 OS << "Mem: 0+#" << getMemIndexReg() << "+" << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
441 break; 0
442 case k_MemoryZeroImmImm: 0
443 assert(getMemIndex() != nullptr && getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
444 OS << "Mem: 0+" << *getMemIndex() << "+" << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
445 break; 0
446 case k_MemoryRegImm: 0
447 assert(getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
448 OS << "Mem: #" << getMemBase() << "+" << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
449 break; 0
450 case k_MemoryZeroImm: 0
451 assert(getMemOffset() != nullptr); 0
452 OS << "Mem: 0+" << *getMemOffset() << "\n"; 0
453 break; 0
454 case k_CCOp: 0
455 OS << "CCOp: " << getCCVal() << "\n"; 0
456 break; 0
457 case k_RDOp: 0
458 OS << "RDOp: " << getRDVal() << "\n"; 0
459 break; 0
460 case k_MImmOp: 0
461 OS << "MImm: (" << getMImmVal() << (getM0Flag() ? ")0" : ")1") << "\n"; 0
462 break; 0
463 } ----
464 } 0

513 void addExpr(MCInst &Inst, const MCExpr *Expr) const { 0
514 // Add as immediate when possible. Null MCExpr = 0. ----
515 if (!Expr) 0
516 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); 0
517 else if (const auto *CE = dyn_cast(Expr)) 0
518 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(CE->getValue())); 0
519 else ----
520 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr)); 0
521 } 0

763 ----
764 bool VEAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode, 0
765 OperandVector &Operands, ----
766 MCStreamer &Out, uint64_t &ErrorInfo, ----
767 bool MatchingInlineAsm) { ----
768 MCInst Inst; 0
769 unsigned MatchResult = ----
770 MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, ErrorInfo, MatchingInlineAsm); 0
771 switch (MatchResult) { 0
772 case Match_Success: 0
773 Inst.setLoc(IDLoc); 0
774 Out.emitInstruction(Inst, getSTI()); 0
775 return false; 0
776 ----
777 case Match_MissingFeature: 0
778 return Error(IDLoc, 0
779 "instruction requires a CPU feature not currently enabled"); 0
780 ----
781 case Match_InvalidOperand: { 0
782 SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
783 if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) { 0
784 if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) 0
785 return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction"); 0
786 ----
787 ErrorLoc = ((VEOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc(); 0
788 if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc()) 0
789 ErrorLoc = IDLoc; 0
790 } ----
791 ----
792 return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction"); 0
793 } ----
794 case Match_MnemonicFail: 0
795 return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction mnemonic"); 0
796 } ----
797 llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!"); 0
798 } 0

800 bool VEAsmParser::parseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, SMLoc &StartLoc, 0
801 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
802 if (tryParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc) != MatchOperand_Success) 0
803 return Error(StartLoc, "invalid register name"); 0
804 return false; 0
805 } ----
806 ----
807 /// Parses a register name using a given matching function. ----
808 /// Checks for lowercase or uppercase if necessary. ----
809 int VEAsmParser::parseRegisterName(unsigned (*matchFn)(StringRef)) { 0
810 StringRef Name = Parser.getTok().getString(); 0
811 ----
812 int RegNum = matchFn(Name); 0
813 ----
814 // GCC supports case insensitive register names. All of the VE registers ----
815 // are all lower case. ----
816 if (RegNum == VE::NoRegister) { 0
817 RegNum = matchFn(Name.lower()); 0
818 } ----
819 ----
820 return RegNum; 0
821 } ----
822 ----
823 /// Maps from the set of all register names to a register number. ----
824 /// \note Generated by TableGen. ----
825 static unsigned MatchRegisterName(StringRef Name); ----
826 ----
827 /// Maps from the set of all alternative registernames to a register number. ----
828 /// \note Generated by TableGen. ----
829 static unsigned MatchRegisterAltName(StringRef Name); ----
830 ----
831 OperandMatchResultTy VEAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo, 0
832 SMLoc &StartLoc, ----
833 SMLoc &EndLoc) { ----
834 const AsmToken Tok = Parser.getTok(); 0
835 StartLoc = Tok.getLoc(); 0
836 EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc(); 0
837 RegNo = 0; 0
838 if (getLexer().getKind() != AsmToken::Percent) 0
839 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
840 Parser.Lex(); 0
841 ----
842 RegNo = parseRegisterName(&MatchRegisterName); 0
843 if (RegNo == VE::NoRegister) 0
844 RegNo = parseRegisterName(&MatchRegisterAltName); 0
845 ----
846 if (RegNo != VE::NoRegister) { 0
847 Parser.Lex(); 0
848 return MatchOperand_Success; 0
849 } ----
850 ----
851 getLexer().UnLex(Tok); 0
852 return MatchOperand_NoMatch; 0
853 } 0
854 ----
855 static StringRef parseCC(StringRef Name, unsigned Prefix, unsigned Suffix, 0
856 bool IntegerCC, bool OmitCC, SMLoc NameLoc, ----
857 OperandVector *Operands) { ----
858 // Parse instructions with a conditional code. For example, 'bne' is ----
859 // converted into two operands 'b' and 'ne'. ----
860 StringRef Cond = Name.slice(Prefix, Suffix); 0
861 VECC::CondCode CondCode = ----
862 IntegerCC ? stringToVEICondCode(Cond) : stringToVEFCondCode(Cond); 0
863 ----
864 // If OmitCC is enabled, CC_AT and CC_AF is treated as a part of mnemonic. ----
865 if (CondCode != VECC::UNKNOWN && 0
866 (!OmitCC || (CondCode != VECC::CC_AT && CondCode != VECC::CC_AF))) { 0
867 StringRef SuffixStr = Name.substr(Suffix); 0
868 // Push "b". ----
869 Name = Name.slice(0, Prefix); 0
870 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
871 // Push $cond part. ----
872 SMLoc CondLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(NameLoc.getPointer() + Prefix); 0
873 SMLoc SuffixLoc = SMLoc::getFromPointer(NameLoc.getPointer() + Suffix); 0
874 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateCCOp(CondCode, CondLoc, SuffixLoc)); 0
875 // push suffix like ".l.t" ----
876 if (!SuffixStr.empty()) 0
877 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(SuffixStr, SuffixLoc)); 0
878 } else { 0
879 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
880 } ----
881 return Name; 0
882 } ----
883 ----
884 static StringRef parseRD(StringRef Name, unsigned Prefix, SMLoc NameLoc, 0
885 OperandVector *Operands) { ----
886 // Parse instructions with a conditional code. For example, 'cvt.w.d.sx.rz' ----
887 // is converted into two operands 'cvt.w.d.sx' and '.rz'. ----
888 StringRef RD = Name.substr(Prefix); 0
889 VERD::RoundingMode RoundingMode = stringToVERD(RD); 0
890 ----
891 if (RoundingMode != VERD::UNKNOWN) { 0
892 Name = Name.slice(0, Prefix); 0
893 // push 1st like `cvt.w.d.sx` ----
894 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
895 SMLoc SuffixLoc = ----
896 SMLoc::getFromPointer(NameLoc.getPointer() + (RD.data() - Name.data())); 0
897 SMLoc SuffixEnd = ----
898 SMLoc::getFromPointer(NameLoc.getPointer() + (RD.end() - Name.data())); 0
899 // push $round if it has rounding mode ----
900 Operands->push_back( 0
901 VEOperand::CreateRDOp(RoundingMode, SuffixLoc, SuffixEnd)); 0
902 } else { ----
903 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(Name, NameLoc)); 0
904 } ----
905 return Name; 0
906 } ----
907 ----
908 // Split the mnemonic into ASM operand, conditional code and instruction ----
909 // qualifier (half-word, byte). ----
910 StringRef VEAsmParser::splitMnemonic(StringRef Name, SMLoc NameLoc, 0
911 OperandVector *Operands) { ----
912 // Create the leading tokens for the mnemonic ----
913 StringRef Mnemonic = Name; 0
914 ----
915 if (Name[0] == 'b') { 0
916 // Match b?? or br??. ----
917 size_t Start = 1; 0
918 size_t Next = Name.find('.'); 0
919 // Adjust position of CondCode. ----
920 if (Name.size() > 1 && Name[1] == 'r') 0
921 Start = 2; 0
922 // Check suffix. ----
923 bool ICC = true; 0
924 if (Next + 1 < Name.size() && 0
925 (Name[Next + 1] == 'd' || Name[Next + 1] == 's')) 0
926 ICC = false; 0
927 Mnemonic = parseCC(Name, Start, Next, ICC, true, NameLoc, Operands); 0
928 } else if (Name.startswith("cmov.l.") || Name.startswith("cmov.w.") || 0
929 Name.startswith("cmov.d.") || Name.startswith("cmov.s.")) { 0
930 bool ICC = Name[5] == 'l' || Name[5] == 'w'; 0
931 Mnemonic = parseCC(Name, 7, Name.size(), ICC, false, NameLoc, Operands); 0
932 } else if (Name.startswith("cvt.w.d.sx") || Name.startswith("cvt.w.d.zx") || 0
933 Name.startswith("cvt.w.s.sx") || Name.startswith("cvt.w.s.zx")) { 0
934 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 10, NameLoc, Operands); 0
935 } else if (Name.startswith("cvt.l.d")) { 0
936 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 7, NameLoc, Operands); 0
937 } else if (Name.startswith("vcvt.w.d.sx") || Name.startswith("vcvt.w.d.zx") || 0
938 Name.startswith("vcvt.w.s.sx") || Name.startswith("vcvt.w.s.zx")) { 0
939 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 11, NameLoc, Operands); 0
940 } else if (Name.startswith("vcvt.l.d")) { 0
941 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 8, NameLoc, Operands); 0
942 } else if (Name.startswith("pvcvt.w.s.lo") || 0
943 Name.startswith("pvcvt.w.s.up")) { 0
944 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 12, NameLoc, Operands); 0
945 } else if (Name.startswith("pvcvt.w.s")) { 0
946 Mnemonic = parseRD(Name, 9, NameLoc, Operands); 0
947 } else if (Name.startswith("vfmk.l.") || Name.startswith("vfmk.w.") || 0
948 Name.startswith("vfmk.d.") || Name.startswith("vfmk.s.")) { 0
949 bool ICC = Name[5] == 'l' || Name[5] == 'w' ? true : false; 0
950 Mnemonic = parseCC(Name, 7, Name.size(), ICC, true, NameLoc, Operands); 0
951 } else if (Name.startswith("pvfmk.w.lo.") || Name.startswith("pvfmk.w.up.") || 0
952 Name.startswith("pvfmk.s.lo.") || Name.startswith("pvfmk.s.up.")) { 0
953 bool ICC = Name[6] == 'l' || Name[6] == 'w' ? true : false; 0
954 Mnemonic = parseCC(Name, 11, Name.size(), ICC, true, NameLoc, Operands); 0
955 } else { ----
956 Operands->push_back(VEOperand::CreateToken(Mnemonic, NameLoc)); 0
957 } ----
958 ----
959 return Mnemonic; 0
960 } ----
961 ----
962 static void applyMnemonicAliases(StringRef &Mnemonic, ----
963 const FeatureBitset &Features, ----
964 unsigned VariantID); ----
965 ----
966 bool VEAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info, StringRef Name, 0
967 SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) { ----
968 // If the target architecture uses MnemonicAlias, call it here to parse ----
969 // operands correctly. ----
970 applyMnemonicAliases(Name, getAvailableFeatures(), 0); 0
971 ----
972 // Split name to first token and the rest, e.g. "bgt.l.t" to "b", "gt", and ----
973 // ".l.t". We treat "b" as a mnemonic, "gt" as first operand, and ".l.t" ----
974 // as second operand. ----
975 StringRef Mnemonic = splitMnemonic(Name, NameLoc, &Operands); 0
976 ----
977 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
978 // Read the first operand. ----
979 if (parseOperand(Operands, Mnemonic) != MatchOperand_Success) { 0
980 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
981 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
982 } ----
983 ----
984 while (getLexer().is(AsmToken::Comma)) { 0
985 Parser.Lex(); // Eat the comma. 0
986 // Parse and remember the operand. ----
987 if (parseOperand(Operands, Mnemonic) != MatchOperand_Success) { 0
988 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
989 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
990 } ----
991 } ----
992 } ----
993 if (getLexer().isNot(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) { 0
994 SMLoc Loc = getLexer().getLoc(); 0
995 return Error(Loc, "unexpected token"); 0
996 } ----
997 Parser.Lex(); // Consume the EndOfStatement. 0
998 return false; 0
999 } ----
1000 ----
1001 ParseStatus VEAsmParser::parseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) { 0
1002 std::string IDVal = DirectiveID.getIdentifier().lower(); 0
1003 ----
1004 // Defines VE specific directives. Reference is "Vector Engine Assembly ----
1005 // Language Reference Manual": ----
1006 // https://www.hpc.nec/documents/sdk/pdfs/VectorEngine-as-manual-v1.3.pdf ----
1007 ----
1008 // The .word is 4 bytes long on VE. ----
1009 if (IDVal == ".word") 0
1010 return parseLiteralValues(4, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1011 ----
1012 // The .long is 8 bytes long on VE. ----
1013 if (IDVal == ".long") 0
1014 return parseLiteralValues(8, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1015 ----
1016 // The .llong is 8 bytes long on VE. ----
1017 if (IDVal == ".llong") 0
1018 return parseLiteralValues(8, DirectiveID.getLoc()); 0
1019 ----
1020 // Let the MC layer to handle other directives. ----
1021 return ParseStatus::NoMatch; 0
1022 } 0
1023 ----
1024 /// parseLiteralValues ----
1025 /// ::= .word expression [, expression]* ----
1026 /// ::= .long expression [, expression]* ----
1027 /// ::= .llong expression [, expression]* ----
1028 bool VEAsmParser::parseLiteralValues(unsigned Size, SMLoc L) { 0
1029 auto parseOne = [&]() -> bool { 0
1030 const MCExpr *Value; ----
1031 if (getParser().parseExpression(Value)) 0
1032 return true; 0
1033 getParser().getStreamer().emitValue(Value, Size, L); 0
1034 return false; 0
1035 }; 0
1036 return (parseMany(parseOne)); 0
1037 } ----
1038 ----
1039 /// Extract \code @lo32/@hi32/etc \endcode modifier from expression. ----
1040 /// Recursively scan the expression and check for VK_VE_HI32/LO32/etc ----
1041 /// symbol variants. If all symbols with modifier use the same ----
1042 /// variant, return the corresponding VEMCExpr::VariantKind, ----
1043 /// and a modified expression using the default symbol variant. ----
1044 /// Otherwise, return NULL. ----
1045 const MCExpr * ----
1046 VEAsmParser::extractModifierFromExpr(const MCExpr *E, 0
1047 VEMCExpr::VariantKind &Variant) { ----
1048 MCContext &Context = getParser().getContext(); 0
1049 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_None; 0
1050 ----
1051 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
1052 case MCExpr::Target: 0
1053 case MCExpr::Constant: ----
1054 return nullptr; 0
1055 ----
1056 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: { 0
1057 const MCSymbolRefExpr *SRE = cast(E); 0
1058 ----
1059 switch (SRE->getKind()) { 0
1060 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_None: 0
1061 // Use VK_VE_REFLONG to a symbol without modifiers. ----
1062 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_REFLONG; 0
1063 break; 0
1064 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_HI32: 0
1065 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_HI32; 0
1066 break; 0
1067 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_LO32: 0
1068 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_LO32; 0
1069 break; 0
1070 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_PC_HI32: 0
1071 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_PC_HI32; 0
1072 break; 0
1073 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_PC_LO32: 0
1074 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_PC_LO32; 0
1075 break; 0
1076 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_GOT_HI32: 0
1077 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_GOT_HI32; 0
1078 break; 0
1079 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_GOT_LO32: 0
1080 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_GOT_LO32; 0
1081 break; 0
1082 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_GOTOFF_HI32: 0
1083 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_GOTOFF_HI32; 0
1084 break; 0
1085 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_GOTOFF_LO32: 0
1086 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_GOTOFF_LO32; 0
1087 break; 0
1088 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_PLT_HI32: 0
1089 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_PLT_HI32; 0
1090 break; 0
1091 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_PLT_LO32: 0
1092 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_PLT_LO32; 0
1093 break; 0
1094 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_TLS_GD_HI32: 0
1095 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_TLS_GD_HI32; 0
1096 break; 0
1097 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_TLS_GD_LO32: 0
1098 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_TLS_GD_LO32; 0
1099 break; 0
1100 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_TPOFF_HI32: 0
1101 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_TPOFF_HI32; 0
1102 break; 0
1103 case MCSymbolRefExpr::VK_VE_TPOFF_LO32: 0
1104 Variant = VEMCExpr::VK_VE_TPOFF_LO32; 0
1105 break; 0
1106 default: 0
1107 return nullptr; 0
1108 } ----
1109 ----
1110 return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(&SRE->getSymbol(), Context); 0
1111 } ----
1112 ----
1113 case MCExpr::Unary: { 0
1114 const MCUnaryExpr *UE = cast(E); 0
1115 const MCExpr *Sub = extractModifierFromExpr(UE->getSubExpr(), Variant); 0
1116 if (!Sub) 0
1117 return nullptr; 0
1118 return MCUnaryExpr::create(UE->getOpcode(), Sub, Context); 0
1119 } ----
1120 ----
1121 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
1122 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(E); 0
1123 VEMCExpr::VariantKind LHSVariant, RHSVariant; ----
1124 const MCExpr *LHS = extractModifierFromExpr(BE->getLHS(), LHSVariant); 0
1125 const MCExpr *RHS = extractModifierFromExpr(BE->getRHS(), RHSVariant); 0
1126 ----
1127 if (!LHS && !RHS) 0
1128 return nullptr; 0
1129 ----
1130 if (!LHS) 0
1131 LHS = BE->getLHS(); 0
1132 if (!RHS) 0
1133 RHS = BE->getRHS(); 0
1134 ----
1135 if (LHSVariant == VEMCExpr::VK_VE_None) 0
1136 Variant = RHSVariant; 0
1137 else if (RHSVariant == VEMCExpr::VK_VE_None) 0
1138 Variant = LHSVariant; 0
1139 else if (LHSVariant == RHSVariant) 0
1140 Variant = LHSVariant; 0
1141 else ----
1142 return nullptr; 0
1143 ----
1144 return MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS, Context); 0
1145 } ----
1146 } ----
1147 ----
1148 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
1149 } ----
1150 ----
1151 const MCExpr *VEAsmParser::fixupVariantKind(const MCExpr *E) { 0
1152 MCContext &Context = getParser().getContext(); 0
1153 ----
1154 switch (E->getKind()) { 0
1155 case MCExpr::Target: 0
1156 case MCExpr::Constant: ----
1157 case MCExpr::SymbolRef: ----
1158 return E; 0
1159 ----
1160 case MCExpr::Unary: { 0
1161 const MCUnaryExpr *UE = cast(E); 0
1162 const MCExpr *Sub = fixupVariantKind(UE->getSubExpr()); 0
1163 if (Sub == UE->getSubExpr()) 0
1164 return E; 0
1165 return MCUnaryExpr::create(UE->getOpcode(), Sub, Context); 0
1166 } ----
1167 ----
1168 case MCExpr::Binary: { 0
1169 const MCBinaryExpr *BE = cast(E); 0
1170 const MCExpr *LHS = fixupVariantKind(BE->getLHS()); 0
1171 const MCExpr *RHS = fixupVariantKind(BE->getRHS()); 0
1172 if (LHS == BE->getLHS() && RHS == BE->getRHS()) 0
1173 return E; 0
1174 return MCBinaryExpr::create(BE->getOpcode(), LHS, RHS, Context); 0
1175 } ----
1176 } ----
1177 ----
1178 llvm_unreachable("Invalid expression kind!"); 0
1179 } ----
1180 ----
1181 /// ParseExpression. This differs from the default "parseExpression" in that ----
1182 /// it handles modifiers. ----
1183 bool VEAsmParser::parseExpression(const MCExpr *&EVal) { 0
1184 // Handle \code symbol @lo32/@hi32/etc \endcode. ----
1185 if (getParser().parseExpression(EVal)) 0
1186 return true; 0
1187 ----
1188 // Convert MCSymbolRefExpr with VK_* to MCExpr with VK_*. ----
1189 EVal = fixupVariantKind(EVal); 0
1190 VEMCExpr::VariantKind Variant; ----
1191 const MCExpr *E = extractModifierFromExpr(EVal, Variant); 0
1192 if (E) 0
1193 EVal = VEMCExpr::create(Variant, E, getParser().getContext()); 0
1194 ----
1195 return false; 0
1196 } ----
1197 ----
1198 OperandMatchResultTy VEAsmParser::parseMEMOperand(OperandVector &Operands) { 0
1199 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "parseMEMOperand\n"); 0
